Output shape (write to `{{ captions_block_path }}`):

```html
<div id="captions-layer" class="captions-layer">
  <style>
    /* ALL rules prefixed with #captions-layer (no bare class selectors) */
    #captions-layer { position: absolute; inset: 0; pointer-events: none; overflow: visible; }
    #captions-layer .cg { /* per-group styles inherited from DESIGN.md typography + palette */ }
    /* per-word emphasis classes — brand, allcaps, number, cta, emotional */
  </style>
  <!-- one <div class="cg" id="cg-0">…words…</div> per group, all initially opacity:0 -->
  <script>
    (function() {
      // Reference transcript: {{ transcript_json_filename }}
      // The fragment ships its grouping table inline (the transcript JSON is
      // resolved at build time, not fetched at runtime — Phase 4 Pattern A
      // is a single self-contained HTML).
      var GROUPS = [
        // { id: "cg-0", text: "...", start: 0.0, end: 1.2,
        //   words: [{ text, start, end, emphasis: "brand"|"allcaps"|... }] },
        // ...one per caption group
      ];
      window.__captionTimelines = window.__captionTimelines || {};
      var tl = gsap.timeline({ paused: true });
      GROUPS.forEach(function (group) {
        var el = document.getElementById(group.id);
        if (!el) return;
        // Entrance via tl.fromTo (motion-principles.md L115-123 — never tl.from)
        tl.fromTo(el, /* from */ {}, /* to */ {}, group.start);
        // Exit + hard kill (canon §"Caption Exit Guarantee" — non-negotiable)
        tl.to(el, { opacity: 0, scale: 0.95, duration: 0.12, ease: "power2.in" }, group.end - 0.12);
        tl.set(el, { opacity: 0, visibility: "hidden" }, group.end);
      });
      // Self-lint per canon §"Caption Exit Guarantee"
      GROUPS.forEach(function (group, gi) {
        var el = document.getElementById(group.id);
        if (!el) return;
        tl.seek(group.end + 0.01);
        var computed = window.getComputedStyle(el);
        if (computed.opacity !== "0" && computed.visibility !== "hidden") {
          console.warn("[caption-lint] group " + gi + " still visible at t=" + (group.end + 0.01).toFixed(2) + "s");
        }
      });
      tl.seek(0);
      window.__captionTimelines["captions"] = tl;
      // Nest under the root timeline so it advances with the composition's seek.
      var root = window.__timelines && window.__timelines["root"];
      if (root) root.add(tl, 0);
    })();
  </script>
</div>
```

Hard rules (orchestrator-house, derived from canon — surfaced so you don't miss them):
- **Read DESIGN.md first.** Captions inherit typography (font-family, weight) and palette
  (foreground + accent) from the design system. Do not pick fonts/colors out of canon.
- **Reference `{{ transcript_json_filename }}` in the HTML** (a comment is enough). This
  is the precondition for `gate:captions_track` to detect the captions track.
- **`tl.set(...)` deterministic kill at `group.end` for every group.** Canon §"Caption
  Exit Guarantee" — non-negotiable.
- **`position: absolute` on the captions container.** Never `position: relative`. Never
  `left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%)` on the container — clips at composition edges.
- **One caption group visible at a time.** Word grouping per canon: 2–3 words for hype,
  3–5 for conversational, 4–6 for measured/calm — choose the band from the detected tone.
- **CSS scoping**: every rule prefixed with `#captions-layer`. No bare class selectors.
- **`tl.fromTo()` for entrances** (motion-principles.md L115-123). Never `tl.from()`,
  never bare `gsap.from()`. Non-linear seek breaks otherwise.
- **Determinism**: no `Math.random()`, no `Date.now()`. Group/word arrays are static
  literals in the script.
- **No `<script src="..."`>** — root scaffold supplies GSAP once.
- **Avoid the literal substring `repeat:` followed by ` -1`** (HF lint regex
  false-positive). Use `repeat: 999` or omit.

Process:
1. `Read` `{{ design_md_path }}` for typography + palette.
2. `Read` `{{ transcript_json_path }}` for the word stream and detect tone.
3. `Read` the canon list above (mandatory; do not rely on memory).
4. Group words per §"Word Grouping" using the band that matches the detected tone.
5. Apply per-word emphasis per §"Per-Word Styling" — brand/product names, ALL CAPS,
   numbers/statistics, emotional keywords, calls-to-action.
6. `Write` ONE file to `{{ captions_block_path }}` containing the fragment shape above.
7. Reply on a single line: `Wrote {{ captions_block_path }} (<N> groups, tone=<profile>).`

Do NOT modify the root `index.html`, do NOT touch sibling `compositions/*.html`, do NOT
add `<script src=...>` tags. Stay inside the captions block.
